---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import FloatingActionButton from '../../components/FloatingActionButton.astro';
import BlogContactCTA from '../../components/BlogContactCTA.astro';

const blogPost = {
    title: "A New Journey, A New Team: Building a Culture That Thrives",
    date: "February 28, 2025",
    author: "Jonathon Broce"
};
---

<Layout title={`${blogPost.title} - Day 41 Thrive`}>
    <Header />
    <main class="blog-post">
        <article class="container">
            <header class="post-header">
                <h1>{blogPost.title}</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span class="date">{blogPost.date}</span>
                    <span class="author">By {blogPost.author}</span>
                </div>
            </header>
            <div class="post-content">
                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p>Every new journey begins with a vision. It starts with an idea, a purpose, and the belief that something incredible can be built from the ground up. But here's the truth—vision alone isn't enough. Success isn't just about what you build; it's about who you build it with.</p>
                
                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, we're stepping into a new chapter with a new team, but we aren't starting from scratch. We're bringing with us the lessons, the experiences, and the values that have shaped past successes. We've seen firsthand what happens when you build the culture first, when you prioritize core values, and when you create a team that is more than just a group of people working together—it's a team that thrives together.</p>
                
                <p>This isn't just a new beginning. It's the next evolution. And we're ready—not just to survive, but to help every client, partner, and team member thrive.</p>

                <h2>The Power of Building the Culture First</h2>
                <p>If there's one lesson we've learned from past successes, it's this: culture isn't an afterthought—it's the foundation.</p>
                
                <p>A team without culture is like a house without a frame. No matter how good the materials are, no matter how strong the vision is, without the right structure, it won't stand. Culture defines:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>How we show up every day.</li>
                    <li>How we treat our clients and each other.</li>
                    <li>How we handle challenges, setbacks, and victories.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, our culture is built on three key pillars:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Resilience</strong> – We embrace challenges, face adversity head-on, and push through the storms instead of running from them.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ownership</strong> – We don't just work a job; we take ownership of our roles, our impact, and the success of our clients.</li>
                    <li><strong>Growth</strong> – Thriving isn't about reaching a finish line; it's about continuous learning, innovation, and pushing each other to be better every day.</li>
                </ol>

                <p>This isn't just a company. This is a movement.</p>

                <h2>The Core Values That Shape Us</h2>
                <p>When you build a team, you don't just hire for skills—you build around values. Skills can be taught, but values? They are what define who we are and how we lead.</p>
                
                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, our core values aren't just words on a wall. They are the foundation of every decision we make and every action we take.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Integrity First</strong> – We do what's right, even when no one is watching.</li>
                    <li><strong>Lead with Purpose</strong> – Leadership isn't about a title; it's about serving others and creating impact.</li>
                    <li><strong>Collaboration Over Competition</strong> – The best ideas come when we work together, not against each other.</li>
                    <li><strong>Results Through Relationships</strong> – Business isn't just about transactions—it's about building trust and long-term success.</li>
                    <li><strong>Passion for Thriving</strong> – We don't just survive. We push for greatness, for our team and for our clients.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>These values aren't negotiable—they are the DNA of our company. And the people who share them? They aren't just employees. They are the reason we will succeed.</p>

                <h2>The Best Team for the Best Clients</h2>
                <p>A great team isn't built by accident. It's built with intention, strategy, and the right people. And at Day 41 Thrive, we aren't just building any team—we are building the best team.</p>
                
                <p>Why? Because we know that when we thrive, our clients thrive.</p>
                
                <p>Every company says they want to help their clients succeed. But at Day 41 Thrive, it's our mission. Our team is designed to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Develop leaders, not just employees.</li>
                    <li>Create solutions that empower businesses to thrive long-term.</li>
                    <li>Be a true partner, guiding companies through challenges and toward success.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>We don't just work for our clients—we work alongside them, ensuring they don't just get by, but that they thrive in every aspect of their business.</p>

                <h2>Harnessing Past Successes to Build a Stronger Future</h2>
                <p>We're not starting from scratch—we're building on a foundation of proven success. The lessons we've learned from past ventures have given us clarity, strategy, and confidence in how to build something great.</p>
                
                <p>What we've learned:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Culture drives performance.</strong> Companies that invest in people first see the biggest wins.</li>
                    <li><strong>Core values define success.</strong> Businesses with strong values create long-term impact, while those without them fall apart under pressure.</li>
                    <li><strong>Resilience is the key to growth.</strong> Setbacks are inevitable, but what separates the best companies from the rest is their ability to push forward and evolve.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Every success we've had, every challenge we've overcome, and every lesson we've learned has prepared us for this moment.</p>

                <h2>Day 41 Stories: A New Beginning with a Proven Foundation</h2>
                <p>Starting a new journey is exciting, but it's also filled with challenges. In the early stages of building this team, one thing became crystal clear:</p>
                
                <p>The right people make all the difference.</p>
                
                <p>The moment we started bringing in the right team members—people who believed in the mission, who shared the vision, who lived the core values—everything started to align.</p>
                
                <p>This team? It's different. It's built on trust, passion, and the belief that we're here to do something that matters.</p>
                
                <p>This isn't just another company launch. This is the start of something that will change lives—ours, our clients', and the people we impact along the way.</p>

                <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                <p>A new journey always brings excitement, but what makes this one special is the people who are on it with us.</p>
                
                <p>We are building something great—not just because of a strong vision, but because of a strong team.</p>
                
                <p>We've learned from past successes, we've built a foundation of culture and values first, and now we are ready.</p>
                
                <p>Ready to lead.<br>
                Ready to serve.<br>
                Ready to thrive.</p>
                
                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, we don't just help our clients survive—we help them thrive. And with this team, there's no limit to what we can achieve.</p>
                
                <BlogContactCTA />
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
    <FloatingActionButton />
</Layout>

<style>
    .blog-post {
        padding-top: 80px;
    }

    .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .post-header {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--primary);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .post-meta {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 1rem;
        color: var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    .post-content {
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .post-content h2 {
        color: var(--primary);
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    }

    .post-content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .post-content ul,
    .post-content ol {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .post-content li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .post-content strong {
        color: var(--primary);
    }
</style>